article.headline: Austin Peay 62, Evansville 54
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Anthony Davis scored 26 points as Austin Peay gave coach David Loos his 200th win at the school Monday night with a 62-54 victory over Evansville. The Governors (2-2) led all the way in a defensive first half, taking a 25-16 lead into the break before the Aces (0-3) mounted a second-half comeback. Austin Peay stretched its lead to 34-20 with 17:20 left on a 3-pointer by Rhet Wierzba and a bucket by Davis. Evansville went on a 21-6 run to take the lead at 41-40 with 10:26 to play on a layup by Dewayne Lee. But Austin Peay got the ball inside to Josh Lewis, who finished with 10 points, for a layup and Adrian Henning followed with a three-point play to give the Governors the lead for good at 45-41. Evansville never got within four points the rest of the game. Henning scored 15 points for the Governors and Lewis had eight rebounds. Andre Burton led the Aces with 23 points, while Lee had 15 points and six boards. Neither team shot well from 3-point range. Austin Peay was 1-for-14 and Evansville was 2-for-10.
